  "prompt": "Is there a maximum limit for a transaction via Net Banking through an SBI account?",
  "response": "Yes, the State Bank of India (SBI) has specific limits on transactions via net banking, depending on the type of transfer and the account holder's profile. For instance, for Personal Banking, the transaction limit can vary. Here are some general guidelines:\n\n1. **NEFT (National Electronic Funds Transfer)**: There's generally no maximum transaction limit, but individual banks may impose their own limits. For SBI, the limit for NEFT transactions through net banking is typically up to Rs. 10 lakhs per transaction.\n\n2. **RTGS (Real Time Gross Settlement)**: The minimum amount for an RTGS transaction is Rs. 2 lakhs, and the maximum limit is up to Rs. 10 lakhs per transaction through net banking for retail customers.\n\n3. **IMPS (Immediate Payment Service)**: The transaction limit for IMPS is generally up to Rs. 2 lakhs per transaction.\n\n4. **UPI (Unified Payments Interface)**: The maximum limit per transaction is usually Rs. 1 lakh, though this can vary.\n\nThese limits can be subject to change, and they can also vary based on the customer's relationship with the bank (corporate accounts, high net worth individuals, etc., may have different limits). For precise and the most up-to-date information, it is recommended to check directly with SBI or refer to their official guidelines on internet banking transaction limits.",
